---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Uses | Joe Karlsson"
	description="Hardware, software, and gear I use daily for development, content creation, and my homelab."
	schemaType="WebPage"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8">
		<p class="mb-2 font-mono text-sm text-coral" aria-hidden="true">~$ cat uses.md</p>
		<h1 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold text-coral md:text-4xl">Uses</h1>
		<p class="mb-4 text-gray-400">
			Hardware, software, and gear I use daily for development, content creation, and running my
			homelab.
		</p>
		<div class="mb-8 rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 px-5 py-4">
			<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
				This is a living document - I update it as my setup evolves. Things get swapped out, new
				tools earn a permanent spot, and old favorites get retired. If something here looks
				outdated, it probably means I haven't gotten around to updating this page yet.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">Last updated: March 2026</p>
		</div>

		<!-- View Toggle -->
		<div class="mb-8 flex gap-0 font-mono text-sm" role="tablist" aria-label="View mode">
			<button
				id="tab-normal"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="true"
				aria-controls="normal-view"
				class="rounded-l-md border border-surface-3 bg-coral px-4 py-2 text-black transition-colors"
				onclick="switchView('normal')"
			>
				view: normal
			</button>
			<button
				id="tab-apt"
				role="tab"
				aria-selected="false"
				aria-controls="apt-view"
				class="rounded-r-md border border-l-0 border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 px-4 py-2 text-gray-400 transition-colors"
				onclick="switchView('apt')"
			>
				view: apt list --installed
			</button>
		</div>

		<div id="normal-view">
			<img
				src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2685.webp"
				alt="Joe Karlsson's desk setup"
				class="mb-10 w-full rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
				width="1200"
				height="675"
				loading="eager"
			/>

			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<!-- 1. Desk & Hardware                         -->
			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-bold text-white">
					<span class="text-coral font-mono text-sm" aria-hidden="true">~$</span> ls hardware/
				</h2>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3">computer & monitors</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.apple.com/macbook-pro/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">MacBook Pro M3 Pro</a
								></strong
							> - 36 GB RAM. A massive upgrade from the M1 Air - the extra cores and memory make a real
							difference for Docker, multiple IDEs, and running local AI models.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white">Monitors</strong> - <a
								href="https://www.amazon.com/Lenovo-ThinkVision-P27h-10-LED-Monitor/dp/B071DK1TW8"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">ThinkVision P27h-10</a
							> 27" QHD (right) + <a
								href="https://www.amazon.com/Dell-U2723QE-UltraSharp-USB-C-Monitor/dp/B09TQZP9CL"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Dell U3417W</a
							> 34" 4K (left). If I were buying today, I'd go ultrawide.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.ergotron.com/en-us/products/product-details/45-245"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Ergotron LX Dual Monitor Arm</a
								></strong
							> - lets me reposition monitors based on what I'm working on and frees up desk space for
							hardware projects.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.amazon.com/Dell-452-BCYT-D6000-Universal-Black/dp/B071YTQBXM"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Dell Universal Dock D6000</a
								></strong
							> - bought used on eBay for under $100. Single USB-C cable for power, monitors, and all
							USB accessories.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">input & peripherals</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.razer.com/pc/gaming-mice/deathadder-line"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Razer DeathAdder Chroma</a
								></strong
							> - gaming mouse.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.apple.com/shop/product/MK2C3LL/A/magic-trackpad"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Apple Magic Trackpad 2</a
								></strong
							> - for swipe and pinch controls.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.razer.com/gaming-mouse-mats/razer-goliathus-extended-chroma"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Razer Goliathus Extended Chroma</a
								></strong
							> - mousepad with RGB backlighting.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">keyboards</p>
				<img
					src="/images/blog/how-i-work/5422ABA8-496F-41FD-83A0-E04FD7807046-1024x823.webp"
					alt="Joe's mechanical keyboards"
					class="mb-4 w-full rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
					width="1024"
					height="823"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B072LZ2YRM"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Vortexgear Race 3</a
								></strong
							> - with Cherry MX Clear switches.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://vortexgear.store/products/the-new-pok3r-rgb"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Custom Vortex POK3R</a
								></strong
							> - wood case, Cherry MX Blue switches, custom keycap set from WASD Keyboards. I like clicky
							switches - Blues are the loudest and clickiest. I'd recommend Clears as a good starter switch.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">desk & audio</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white">Standing Desk</strong> - custom-built IKEA desktop on industrial
							black steel legs, with a Luna Standing Desk Stool.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.amazon.com/Sony-MDR7506-Professional-Diaphragm-Headphone/dp/B000AJIF4E"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Sony MDR7506</a
								></strong
							> - professional headphones with upgraded velvet pads. Affordable, comfortable, and sound
							great.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.bestbuy.com/site/philips-hue-play-white-color-ambiance-smart-led-bar-light-2-pack-multicolor/6298635.p"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Philips Hue Play</a
								></strong
							> - White & Color Ambiance LED Bar Lights (2-Pack) for desk backlighting.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
					<img
						src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2687-1024x576.webp"
						alt="Desk setup angle 1"
						class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
						width="1024"
						height="576"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
					<img
						src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2688-1024x576.webp"
						alt="Desk setup angle 2"
						class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
						width="1024"
						height="576"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<!-- 2. Recording & Content                     -->
			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-bold text-white">
					<span class="text-coral font-mono text-sm" aria-hidden="true">~$</span> ls recording/
				</h2>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3">camera & audio</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.obsbot.com/obsbot-tiny-2"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">OBSBOT Tiny 2</a
								></strong
							> - 4K AI-powered webcam with gesture control and auto-tracking. Replaced my Sony A6600
							- much simpler setup for Zoom calls and recordings.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.elgato.com/us/en/p/wave-3-black"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Wave:3</a
								></strong
							> - USB condenser mic, managed through <a
								href="https://www.elgato.com/us/en/s/wave-link"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Wave Link</a
							> for mixing. Replaced the Blue Yeti - much better sound and integrates with the Elgato
							ecosystem.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">streaming & recording</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.elgato.com/en/gaming/stream-deck"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Stream Deck</a
								></strong
							> - I use this more for productivity shortcuts than streaming. Scene switching in OBS, muting/unmuting
							in Zoom, launching common workflows, and triggering Home Assistant scenes from my desk.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://obsproject.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">OBS</a
								></strong
							> - for livestreams and conference talk recordings. I have scenes set up for coding demos,
							slides, and picture-in-picture with the green screen.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.techsmith.com/camtasia.html"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Camtasia</a
								></strong
							> - my go-to for editing tutorial videos. Not as powerful as Premiere, but way faster for
							the record-edit-export workflow I need for tech content.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.screen.studio/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Screen Studio</a
								></strong
							> - makes screen recordings look polished with auto-zoom and smooth cursor following. I
							use this for short social media clips and demo GIFs.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://xnipapp.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Xnip</a
								></strong
							> - screenshot tool with annotations and scrolling capture. The scrolling capture is the
							killer feature - great for grabbing full terminal output or long web pages for blog posts.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">lighting & green screen</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07L755X9G"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Key Lights</a
								> (x2)</strong
							> - plus professional studio LED panels.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00JSAOGWG"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Fancierstudio Collapsible Green/Blue Screen</a
								></strong
							> - on a <a
								href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00PLEX7Q4"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Fovitec 7'6" Clip Stand</a
							>.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<!-- 3. Dev Tools & Software                    -->
			<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-bold text-white">
					<span class="text-coral font-mono text-sm" aria-hidden="true">~$</span> ls dev-tools/
				</h2>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3">editors</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://code.visualstudio.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Visual Studio Code</a
								></strong
							> - still my primary editor. Monokai theme + <a
								href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vscode-icons-team.vscode-icons"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">vscode-icons</a
							>.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.cursor.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Cursor</a
								></strong
							> - AI-powered fork of VS Code, increasingly my go-to for new projects.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white">Key extensions</strong> - <a
								href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eamodio.gitlens"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitLens</a
							>, <a
								href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Prettier</a
							> + <a
								href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">ESLint</a
							>, <a
								href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=github.copilot-chat"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitHub Copilot</a
							>, Docker, Remote SSH, Go/Python/Svelte support.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">ai tools</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Claude Code</a
								> (CLI)</strong
							> - my primary coding companion. I use it in the terminal for everything from infrastructure
							automation to building this website. It manages my homelab, writes deployment scripts, and
							helps debug across 40+ containers. I wrote about <a
								href="/blog/building-a-claude-code-blog-skill-what-i-learned-systematizing-content-creation/"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">building a Claude Code blog skill</a
							> for this site.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://claude.ai/download"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Claude</a
								> desktop app</strong
							> - writing, research, and brainstorming.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://github.com/features/copilot"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitHub Copilot</a
								></strong
							> - inline code completion in VS Code and Cursor.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://superwhisper.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">superwhisper</a
								></strong
							> - local speech-to-text, great for dictating docs and messages.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://wakatime.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">WakaTime</a
								></strong
							> - like a Fitbit for programmers, automated time tracking and metrics.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">terminal</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://iterm2.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
									class="text-coral hover:text-teal">iTerm2</a
								></strong
							> - with <a
								href="https://ohmyz.sh/"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Oh My Zsh</a
							> and <a
								href="https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Powerlevel10k</a
							> theme. Plugins: git, z, zsh-autosuggestions, zsh-syntax-highlighting.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white">Dotfiles</strong> - config files at my <a
								href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/dotfiles"
								target="_blank"
								rel="noopener noreferrer"
								class="text-coral hover:text-teal">dotfiles repo</a
							> on GitHub.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="text-xs font-mono text-teal mb-3 mt-6">productivity</p>
				<div class="divide-y divide-surface-3/50">
					<div class="py-3">
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
							<strong class="text-white"
								><a
									href="https://www.raycast.com/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer"
